 line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I love working. Even if I got the =
fattest UBI check, I would continue to read, write, talk to smart people, a=
nd invest. But there&#8217;s plenty of stuff I don&#8217;t like about worki=
ng. If AI can eliminate all of that so I can focus on what I love, bring it=
 on.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">As more people spend more time on the thing=
s they love doing at work &#8211; building things, spending time with custo=
mers, focusing for hours (or days) on really hard problems &#8211; they&#82=
17;ll be more productive, and generate more value.&#160;</p><p style=3D"col=
or: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;"><span>As companies stop wasting money on software seats they don&#8217;t=
 use and travel booking fees they don&#8217;t need to pay, they can hire </=
span><em>more </em><span>of these more productive people to do the very hum=
an things that add value.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>It&#8217;=
s an anti-Private Equity way of making a business more profitable: making e=
ach employee happier and more productive such that companies can hire </spa=
n><em>more </em><span>of them to add more value. </span><a href=3D"https://=
substack.com/redirect/b4c8410f-6aa4-411b-bbbb-94c46b72e9fd?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAw=
Z3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb=
(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Jevons Paradox</a><span> is a he=
ll of a drug.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size=
: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Plus, more talented people =
might start their own companies if they just need to be really good at the =
thing that they&#8217;re good, and not also good at all the undifferentiate=
d work that comes with keeping a company running.&#160;</p><p style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
">More value might flow to the companies that care about crafting great pro=
ducts and delivering great value when agents with tons of data help make pu=
rchasing decisions.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px;=
 line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>There are tons of second and=
 third order effects in the world in which Ramp succeeds in making companie=
s more profitable, not the least of which is that profits can be reinvested=
 in growth, and </span><strong>growth is good</strong><span>.&#160;&#160;</=
span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: =
26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">And what&#8217;s a business that quite literally=
 makes every other business more profitable worth?&#160;</p><p style=3D"col=
or: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;">Man, I don&#8217;t know. A lot.</p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px;"><hr style=3D"background: #dde3e6; border: none; height: 1px; =
